caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 3.

Adocimus
(
Belonotus
) 
nitidululus


comb. nov.

, orig. A, E–G: lectotype of 

Brachypterus nitidulus

, male from Malay Peninsula (“Perak…”); B, C, D, H: lectotype of 

Cillaeus modiglianii

, female from Sumatra (“… Si 
-
Rambé…” = Sirambas); 
A
: body dorsal; 
B
: body of dorsal; 
C
: head, dorsal; 
D
: head and thorax, ventral; 
E
: male anal sclerite, ventral; 
F
: tegmen, ventral; 
G
: penis trunk, dorsal; 
H
: ovipositor, ventral. Scale bars: 
a
= 1.0 mm to Figs A and B; 
b
= 1.0 mm to Figs C and D; 
с
= 0.3 mm to Fig. E and 0.25 mm to Figs F–H.
